transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hey, Jimmy. My name is also Jimmy. I'm one of your customers and I placed an order a week or so ago.

Speaker 1: And I believe, I forget the name of the gentleman I spoke to, but I believe I ordered 10 tablets of the SCORE Blue.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: And if I'm not mistaken, while we were discussing the order, he asked me if I wanted to increase it by 10 more.

Speaker 2: And he'd give me an additional price for the extra 10 and I thought I said yes, do that.

Speaker 1: But I just got my order today in the mail and there's just 10 tablets in the bottle.

Speaker 2: And I just wanted to make sure that I didn't get billed for those extra 10 because I did not get the 10 tablets.

Speaker 1: No, you did not get billed for the extra 10. You just paid for the actual 10 that comes with the first order.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So you paid for 10 and you got 10.

Speaker 2: I'm pretty sure that he offered me I could do an additional 10 and I thought I said yes.

Speaker 1: James, you spoke to me actually. I'm the one that took your order.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah. I was sure you said no, not at this time because you wanted to try these first.

Speaker 2: Okay, then you're correct. I remember you asking me if I wanted to make an additional purchase.

Speaker 1: For a little bit reduced price and I thought maybe I said, but okay, you're great. I got it today.

Speaker 2: I haven't, of course, had a chance to even try them out and won't for a while.

Speaker 1: Because my lady friend that's coming to live with me is not going to be here for another month.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: But anyway, that's all I wanted to know. Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Not a problem. You take care.

Speaker 1: And I'll stay in touch.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right. See you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
